Job Description:
Sirius XM Radio, Inc. seeks Manager Sales Research Analytics in Oakland, CA.
 Job Duties: Design advanced customized SQL queries for third party vendor exposure files. Create unique automated exposure file processes for different vendors which require the utilization of a custom-made Python script. Devise technological processes that streamline team productivity and efficiency. Respond to ad hoc campaign reporting requests by utilizing SQL queries, analyzing Excel data, and assessing advertiser needs and KPIs. Utilize SQL, Tableau and Hive conductor to automate and maintain Tableau dashboards. Identify and address origin of technical issues within exposure files by using advanced proficiency in SQL and Python. Organize and conduct team Python training.
Minimum Requirements: Bachelor’s degree, or foreign equivalent, in Computer Science, Operations Research, Engineering (any field), or closely related quantitative discipline and six (6) months of experience in job offered or six (6) months of experience in the field of data analytics or operations research. 
Special Skills:
Python;
R;
Matlab;
Bash;
SQL;
Data Analysis;
Data Mining;
Tableau;
AWS;
Google Analytics.
Any suitable combination of education, training and experience is acceptable. Education, experience and criminal background checks will be conducted.
Apply online and upload resume to the SXM careers website (https://jobs.jobvite.com/siriusxm).
